- ♪ Yes, I can ♪
- ♪ Can you follow what I'm doing? ♪

1015
00:57:56,506 --> 00:57:58,247
- ♪ Yes, I can ♪
- ♪ Can you scream? Can you shout? ♪

1016
00:57:58,274 --> 00:58:00,845
Come on, Chilly.
You can do it.

1017
00:58:00,877 --> 00:58:03,483
♪ Three, two, one,
this is the countdown ♪

1018
00:58:03,513 --> 00:58:05,356
♪ You know
I won't let you down ♪

1019
00:58:05,381 --> 00:58:07,725
♪ Let's keep going another round... ♪

1020
00:58:07,750 --> 00:58:08,990
Yes!

1021
00:58:10,253 --> 00:58:12,199
♪ Yeah, this is the countdown ♪

1022
00:58:12,222 --> 00:58:14,065
♪ You know
I won't let you down ♪

1023
00:58:14,090 --> 00:58:16,229
♪ Let's keep going another round ♪

1024
00:58:16,259 --> 00:58:18,603
♪ L'ma hit you with
the five, four, three, two, one. ♪

1025
00:58:39,115 --> 00:58:40,822
(toy squeaking )

1026
00:58:40,850 --> 00:58:44,320
We're supposed to be working,
not playing with toys.

1027
00:58:44,354 --> 00:58:46,630
This is all the stuff
we stole from the pet store.

1028
00:58:46,656 --> 00:58:49,068
I thought the dogs could
play with it on the flight.

1029
00:58:49,092 --> 00:58:50,935
Oh, check this out, man.
It's a dog whistle.

1030
00:58:50,960 --> 00:58:52,735
Can you hear anything
on that microphone?

1031
00:58:52,762 --> 00:58:54,708
I can't tell what those kids
are up to in there.

1032
00:58:54,731 --> 00:58:56,540
Well, yeah.
Bobby and Kizzy and Caps

1033
00:58:56,566 --> 00:58:58,239
are teaching Chilly
a bunch of new tricks

1034
00:58:58,268 --> 00:59:00,714
so he could be an indoor dog
so Bobby could take him to New York.

1035
00:59:00,737 --> 00:59:02,683
Wait, you even know
their names?

1036
00:59:02,705 --> 00:59:05,447
Well, yeah. Keeping Chilly
is Bobby's Christmas miracle wish.

1037
00:59:05,475 --> 00:59:07,250
I really hope it comes true.

1038
00:59:07,277 --> 00:59:09,154
You idiot,
we're gangsters.

1039
00:59:09,178 --> 00:59:11,852
It's our job to make sure
the kid's wish doesn't come true.

1040
00:59:11,881 --> 00:59:14,589
You mean in this scenario
we're the Grinch?

1041
00:59:14,617 --> 00:59:16,961
If that kid talks his dad into
bringing that mutt to New York,

1042
00:59:16,986 --> 00:59:19,899
then we can't steal it.
Then we don't get our money.

1043
00:59:19,923 --> 00:59:21,903
That's not to mention
all the nasty things

1044
00:59:21,925 --> 00:59:24,963
Quarterman will do to us
if we screw this deal up.

1045
00:59:29,098 --> 00:59:30,441
( Puffs )

1046
00:59:30,466 --> 00:59:33,640
-( whistle squeals)
-( Chilly whining)

1047
00:59:35,705 --> 00:59:36,877
( Puffs )

1048
00:59:36,906 --> 00:59:38,908
-( whistle squeals)
-( whines, barks)

1049
00:59:44,714 --> 00:59:46,557
It doesn't even work.
What a rip-off.

1050
00:59:46,583 --> 00:59:48,290
( laughs)

1051
00:59:48,318 --> 00:59:50,320
Now that's odd.

1052
00:59:50,353 --> 00:59:52,355
Hey, blow the whistle again.

1053
00:59:52,388 --> 00:59:53,958
But it doesn't make a sound.
Hello.

1054
00:59:53,990 --> 00:59:56,903
It makes a sound at a frequency
only dogs can hear.

1055
00:59:56,926 --> 00:59:58,599
Just blow it!

1056
00:59:58,628 --> 00:59:59,800
( Puffs )

1057
00:59:59,829 --> 01:00:02,173
-( whistle squeals)
-( whines)

1058
01:00:10,306 --> 01:00:12,343
( snarls )

1059
01:00:12,375 --> 01:00:15,322
-( laughing )
- What? What is it?

1060
01:00:15,345 --> 01:00:17,916
Oh, I think I found a way

1061
01:00:17,947 --> 01:00:20,791
of making our little
Christmas miracle come true.

1062
01:00:28,658 --> 01:00:31,798
It's not even Christmas Eve.
Why are we making a fancy dinner?

1063
01:00:31,828 --> 01:00:33,705
Because we are
gonna be spending

1064
01:00:33,730 --> 01:00:36,176
most of our Christmas Day
packing up for the move, buddy.

1065
01:00:36,199 --> 01:00:38,941
And I wanted to spend some
quality time with my favorite guys.

1066
01:00:38,968 --> 01:00:40,845
Gosh, thanks, Lieutenant.

1067
01:00:40,870 --> 01:00:42,781
Well, not you--

1068
01:00:42,805 --> 01:00:45,046
you're welcome, Detective.

1069
01:00:45,074 --> 01:00:46,917
Actually, I'm glad
everybody's here.

1070
01:00:46,943 --> 01:00:49,048
Bingo, by the way.

1071
01:00:49,078 --> 01:00:52,525
After dinner I've got some
pretty cool things to show you guys.

1072
01:00:52,548 --> 01:00:55,688
A pretty cool thing, huh?
I can't wait to see that.

1073
01:01:01,524 --> 01:01:02,901
( Barks)

1074
01:01:17,540 --> 01:01:19,952
Everything points
to Quarterman.

1075
01:01:19,976 --> 01:01:21,978
Former New York
stockbroker,

1076
01:01:22,011 --> 01:01:24,013
then a suspect
in a bank fraud scheme.

1077
01:01:24,047 --> 01:01:25,993
He lost everything
and yet he can still afford

1078
01:01:26,015 --> 01:01:27,858
a millionaire's wardrobe
as a locksmith.

1079
01:01:27,884 --> 01:01:29,727
He had access
to the pet store.

1080
01:01:29,752 --> 01:01:32,130
We have no prints,
no physical evidence.

1081
01:01:33,623 --> 01:01:36,365
- This guy looks familiar.
- Only two more days.

1082
01:01:36,392 --> 01:01:39,601
- You're gonna be missed, Cole.
- You too, Stone.

1083
01:01:39,629 --> 01:01:41,631
( Door opens )

1084
01:01:41,664 --> 01:01:43,541
Hey, hey, Bobby, come on,
you know the rules

1085
01:01:43,566 --> 01:01:46,069
- about bringing Chilly into the house.
- Not to worry, Dad.

1086
01:01:46,102 --> 01:01:48,241
You're talking about
the old Chilly Christmas.

1087
01:01:48,271 --> 01:01:51,741
But now I'd like to introduce to you
the new Chilly Christmas-

1088
01:01:51,774 --> 01:01:53,776
indoor dog.

1089
01:01:53,810 --> 01:01:56,723
- Prepare to be amazed.
- Oh, yeah.

1090
01:02:01,884 --> 01:02:04,956
Hand me the dog whistle.
If it does what you say it does,

1091
01:02:04,987 --> 01:02:07,934
he'll probably send him right to
the pound and for $5 we'll get him out.

1092
01:02:07,957 --> 01:02:11,063
It's almost Christmas Eve. Isn't there
another way we could do this?

1093
01:02:11,094 --> 01:02:13,370
Indeed there is. I could stroll
in there, identify you two

1094
01:02:13,396 --> 01:02:15,899
as the thieves that broke into
three dog pounds and a pet store.

1095
01:02:15,932 --> 01:02:18,344
You'll be arrested
and I'll bring in two new blokes

1096
01:02:18,367 --> 01:02:21,473
who are complete imbeciles.
Would you prefer to do it that way?

1097
01:02:21,504 --> 01:02:25,953
And now for the ultimate demonstration
of indoor Chilly'-s talents...

1098
01:02:25,975 --> 01:02:28,717
He will maneuver himself
through the entire living room,

1099
01:02:28,745 --> 01:02:31,282
full speed, without breaking
a single thing.

1100
01:02:31,314 --> 01:02:34,090
That's it, Bobby.
You did it.

1101
01:02:34,117 --> 01:02:36,996
No, Kizzy, we did it.

1102
01:02:45,328 --> 01:02:47,672
I have a feeling
this is gonna be fun.

1103
01:02:47,697 --> 01:02:49,074
( Whistle tweets )

1104
01:02:50,933 --> 01:02:52,503
( high-pitched whistle
squeals )

1105
01:02:52,535 --> 01:02:55,175
- Stone: What's wrong with him?
- Come here. No.

1106
01:02:55,204 --> 01:02:58,014
All: Chilly, where are you going?
Chilly?

1107
01:02:58,040 --> 01:02:59,815
Come on, calm down.
Chilly, Chilly.

1108
01:02:59,842 --> 01:03:01,844
Cole: Okay, I think he wants
to go outside.

1109
01:03:01,878 --> 01:03:04,449
Kids: Come on, Chilly.
Chilly, where are you going?

1110
01:03:04,480 --> 01:03:05,823
No, Chilly, no.

1111
01:03:07,183 --> 01:03:08,992
-( Squealing continues)
- All: Chilly, no. Chilly.

1112
01:03:09,018 --> 01:03:10,725
Cole: All right, all right,
I got him. I got him.

1113
01:03:10,753 --> 01:03:13,359
Wait, I don't got him.
I don't got him.

1114
01:03:16,325 --> 01:03:18,236
(all shouting )

1115
01:03:18,261 --> 01:03:20,207
- Bobby: Chilly, no.
-( crashing )

1116
01:03:20,229 --> 01:03:23,142
- Oh.
- Bobby: Oh, no.

1117
01:03:23,166 --> 01:03:25,339
Not the trophy.

1118
01:03:25,368 --> 01:03:27,439
Perfect.

1119
01:03:28,805 --> 01:03:30,284
(Chilly whimpers)

1120
01:03:35,578 --> 01:03:38,650
Cole: And this is why I think
it's better if he stays outside.

1121
01:03:42,185 --> 01:03:45,997
Mission accomplished.
Let's go.

1122
01:04:35,338 --> 01:04:36,840
( Kisses )

1123
01:04:49,218 --> 01:04:52,062
♪ Oh, Christmas tree ♪

1124
01:04:52,088 --> 01:04:55,228
♪ Oh, Christmas tree... ♪

1125
01:04:55,258 --> 01:04:59,172
♪ Thy leaves are so unchanging ♪

1126
01:04:59,195 --> 01:05:02,369
♪ Oh, Christmas tree ♪

1127
01:05:02,398 --> 01:05:04,901
♪ Oh, Christmas tree... ♪

1128
01:05:06,936 --> 01:05:08,938
(dogs barking )

1129
01:05:08,971 --> 01:05:10,882
Ow.

1130
01:05:10,907 --> 01:05:12,909
That yappy little dog bit me.

1131
01:05:12,942 --> 01:05:14,751
I can't wait to shove them all
onto that cargo.

1132
01:05:14,777 --> 01:05:17,053
- Are all the dogs loaded up?
- Except for Chilly.

1133
01:05:17,079 --> 01:05:20,060
(cell phone ringing )

1134
01:05:20,082 --> 01:05:22,084
Quarterman.

1135
01:05:22,118 --> 01:05:24,598
Wait, the plane's coming now?
That's too soon, sir.

1136
01:05:27,423 --> 01:05:28,925
Understood.

1137
01:05:28,958 --> 01:05:30,938
Good news?

1138
01:05:33,296 --> 01:05:34,832
The plane leaves
in two hours.

1139
01:05:34,864 --> 01:05:37,367
We have to get the Cole dog now
or the whole deal's off.

1140
01:05:37,400 --> 01:05:39,402
Now? It's Christmas Eve.

1141
01:05:39,435 --> 01:05:41,381
That detective is gonna be
at home with the dog.

1142
01:05:41,404 --> 01:05:43,441
And detectives have guns.
I saw it on TV.

1143
01:05:43,472 --> 01:05:45,782
Detective Cole will not be home.

1144
01:05:45,808 --> 01:05:47,412
How?

1145
01:05:47,443 --> 01:05:49,116
Who are you calling?

1146
01:05:49,145 --> 01:05:50,749
The police, of course.

1147
01:05:57,019 --> 01:05:59,625
Bobby, we just got
an anonymous call

1148
01:05:59,655 --> 01:06:02,568
that the dog thieves are gonna
hit up another kennel downtown today,

1149
01:06:02,591 --> 01:06:04,832
so I-.

1150
01:06:04,860 --> 01:06:07,033
What's the matter, buddy?
Sit down.

1151
01:06:12,668 --> 01:06:15,774
You did your best.
Chilly knows that.

1152
01:06:18,874 --> 01:06:21,047
I know. I just...

1153
01:06:22,712 --> 01:06:26,250
wanted to save him.

1154
01:06:26,282 --> 01:06:29,058
You know? Be a hero...

1155
01:06:29,085 --> 01:06:31,622
like you.

1156
01:06:34,590 --> 01:06:36,592
Well...

1157
01:06:36,625 --> 01:06:39,333
you don't got to be anything
but yourself.

1158
01:06:41,731 --> 01:06:43,733
( Cell phone beeps )

1159
01:06:46,402 --> 01:06:50,009
Look, I gotta go. okay?

1160
01:06:50,039 --> 01:06:52,144
Make sure
you lock the door, please?

1161
01:06:53,609 --> 01:06:57,421
( Door opens, closes )

1162
01:07:19,702 --> 01:07:21,704
(dogs barking within )

1163
01:07:25,474 --> 01:07:28,455
There's a kid and a dog.
It's easy.

1164
01:07:28,477 --> 01:07:31,424
Lock the kid in the closet if you
have to, grab the dog and get out.

1165
01:07:31,447 --> 01:07:34,257
And don't even think of
coming back here without him.

1166
01:07:34,283 --> 01:07:36,058
- The kid?
- The dog!

1167
01:07:38,454 --> 01:07:40,195
You had to open your mouth.

1168
01:07:40,222 --> 01:07:43,396
I was just clarifying.
What's wrong with clarifying?

1169
01:07:43,426 --> 01:07:45,428
(dogs barking. Whining)

1170
01:07:45,461 --> 01:07:48,067
( police radio chatter)

1171
01:07:54,170 --> 01:07:56,514
Stone:
Anything?

1172
01:07:58,841 --> 01:08:00,252
Not a peep.

1173
01:08:00,276 --> 01:08:02,483
All clear.

1174
01:08:05,714 --> 01:08:07,250
What is it?

1175
01:08:07,283 --> 01:08:09,763
I don't know.
Something just doesn't feel right.

1176
01:08:11,787 --> 01:08:13,824
Jasper, call the office
and see if you can get a trace

1177
01:08:13,856 --> 01:08:15,699
on who called in
that anonymous tip.

1178
01:08:15,724 --> 01:08:16,930
I'm on it.

1179
01:08:19,261 --> 01:08:22,606
( Sighs )
It's our last lunch together, pal.

1180
01:08:23,632 --> 01:08:25,634
You should have
something good.

1181
01:08:29,772 --> 01:08:32,048
( Gate creaks )

1182
01:08:34,143 --> 01:08:36,646
I'm sorry, pal.
I really thought this could work.

1183
01:08:36,679 --> 01:08:39,819
I wanted this to be
our Christmas miracle,

1184
01:08:39,849 --> 01:08:43,058
like the time it snowed
for the first time in Sunshine Beach.

1185
01:08:45,654 --> 01:08:47,156
I'm really sorry.

1186
01:08:47,189 --> 01:08:49,499
(whines)

1187
01:08:55,698 --> 01:08:58,008
More than anything,
I really wanted to show you

1188
01:08:58,033 --> 01:09:01,446
that I could be as good a friend to you
as you've been to me.

1189
01:09:07,743 --> 01:09:09,654
Claus-sen:
That takes care of the alarm.

1190
01:09:09,678 --> 01:09:11,680
And that takes care
of the phone.

1191
01:09:28,631 --> 01:09:30,668
Come on, Chilly.

1192
01:09:51,587 --> 01:09:54,727
Wow, now this is a beautiful
Christmas tree.

1193
01:09:54,757 --> 01:09:56,759
Shh.

1194
01:09:59,061 --> 01:10:02,406
Oh my gosh, it's one of those
plastic Wiffle ball bats.

1195
01:10:02,431 --> 01:10:04,570
I've always, always wanted
one of these,

1196
01:10:04,600 --> 01:10:06,602
but my mom
couldn't afford it.

1197
01:10:08,103 --> 01:10:10,879
She probably wouldn't be
too proud of me right now.

1198
01:10:10,906 --> 01:10:12,908
For the last time,

1199
01:10:12,942 --> 01:10:16,355
can I please do the job
I've been hired to do

1200
01:10:16,378 --> 01:10:19,291
without being subjected
to your romantic ramblings

1201
01:10:19,315 --> 01:10:22,694
about a stupid holiday
centered around a fat man with a beard,

1202
01:10:22,718 --> 01:10:26,530
when all I want to do
is steal the flipping dog from the kid?

1203
01:10:27,690 --> 01:10:29,966
( Clatters )

1204
01:10:31,227 --> 01:10:33,798
Uh, Merry Christmas?

1205
01:10:35,564 --> 01:10:36,872
Come on, Chilly, run!

1206
01:10:36,899 --> 01:10:38,936
Get him!

1207
01:10:38,968 --> 01:10:40,970
Jasper: All right,
did you say 7th Street?

1208
01:10:41,003 --> 01:10:43,005
All right, copy that.
Thank you very much.

1209
01:10:43,038 --> 01:10:45,040
The tip came
from a cell phone

1210
01:10:45,074 --> 01:10:48,021
somewhere around the 500 block
of 7th Street downtown.

1211
01:10:48,043 --> 01:10:49,750
500 block of 7th Street?

1212
01:10:49,778 --> 01:10:52,520
That's about four blocks
from Quarterman's locksmith office.

1213
01:10:52,548 --> 01:10:55,051
Hey, do you still have
that file on Quarterman?

1214
01:10:55,084 --> 01:10:57,086
Of course.
It's in the car.

1215
01:11:04,927 --> 01:11:06,964
Is that a dog whistle?

1216
01:11:06,996 --> 01:11:09,067
Yes, sir.

1217
01:11:09,098 --> 01:11:11,100
We use them
for silent commands.

1218
01:11:11,133 --> 01:11:14,307
How would that affect a dog
that wasn't used to working with one?

1219
01:11:14,336 --> 01:11:16,247
Depends on the breed, sir.

1220
01:11:17,840 --> 01:11:19,842
Do you mind if I see it
for a second?

1221
01:11:19,875 --> 01:11:22,185
Sure.

1222
01:11:22,211 --> 01:11:24,213
Thank you.

1223
01:11:27,383 --> 01:11:29,989
(dogs barking within )

1224
01:11:32,755 --> 01:11:35,395
What's going on over there?

1225
01:11:35,424 --> 01:11:37,267
